00:20:24,256 --> 00:20:26,726
HI. MY NAME IS LISA LLOYD,

00:20:26,726 --> 00:20:29,228
AND MY COMPANY IS CALLED
TREASURE CHEST PETS.

00:20:29,228 --> 00:20:31,297
I AM SEEKING $150,000

00:20:31,297 --> 00:20:33,666
IN EXCHANGE FOR 20% EQUITY
IN MY COMPANY.

00:20:33,666 --> 00:20:36,202
TREASURE CHEST PETS
IS A NEW, PATENTED LINE

00:20:36,202 --> 00:20:40,039
OF AWARD‐WINNING ORGANIZERS
THAT LOOK LIKE STUFFED ANIMALS

00:20:40,039 --> 00:20:41,640
FOR CHILDREN.

00:20:41,640 --> 00:20:44,710
THE PUPPY HERE HAS A PILLOW
THAT ATTACHES MAGNETICALLY

00:20:44,710 --> 00:20:46,746
WITH DIFFERENT
SECRET SPACES INSIDE.

00:20:46,746 --> 00:20:49,715
SHE HAS POCKETS
IN BOTH OF HER EARS,

00:20:49,715 --> 00:20:52,985
A SECRET DRAWER
THAT'S HIDDEN BEHIND THE PILLOW,

00:20:52,985 --> 00:20:54,420
AND POCKETS ALSO

00:20:54,420 --> 00:20:57,389
ON BOTH SIDES OF THE BODY
FOR STORING MORE GOODIES.

00:20:57,389 --> 00:21:01,093
WHEN THEY'RE ALL DONE PLAYING
AND STORING, THEY PUT 'EM

00:21:01,093 --> 00:21:03,763
RIGHT BACK TOGETHER,
AND IT'S LIKE A SECRET.

00:21:03,763 --> 00:21:06,465
THE MONKEY HERE'S REAL POPULAR
WITH THE BOYS.

00:21:06,465 --> 00:21:08,768
HIS PILLOW HEAD ALSO ATTACHES
MAGNETICALLY.

00:21:08,768 --> 00:21:11,103
THIS ONE OPENS UP LIKE
A TREASURE CHEST INSTEAD.

00:21:11,103 --> 00:21:13,672
THEY'RE MADE OF FOAM,
AND THAT'S HOW THEY'RE ACTUALLY

00:21:13,672 --> 00:21:16,175
MAINTAINING THEIR SHAPE
AND THE CONTINUITY OF A TOY

00:21:16,175 --> 00:21:18,444
WHILE DOING THE FUNCTION
OF AN ORGANIZER.

00:21:18,444 --> 00:21:21,480
OKAY, SO WHAT ARE
THEY GONNA RETAIL FOR?
$19.99.

00:21:21,480 --> 00:21:24,550
WHAT DO THEY COST TO MAKE?
$4.75.

00:21:24,550 --> 00:21:27,553
ARE YOU SELLING THEM TODAY?
I AM. I'M IN
ABOUT 200 STORES NOW.

00:21:27,553 --> 00:21:31,690
WE JUST LAUNCHED. ACTUALLY,
I STARTED TESTING IN THE MALL.

00:21:31,690 --> 00:21:34,460
I SOLD 600 PIECES BY MYSELF‐‐
WORKING VERY LONG HOURS‐‐

00:21:34,460 --> 00:21:37,329
AT $30 TO $19.99, TE‐TESTING
DIFFERENT PRICE POINTS.

00:21:37,329 --> 00:21:41,600
HOW MUCH SALES HAVE YOU DONE
IN ONE YEAR, THE PAST YEAR?

00:21:41,600 --> 00:21:43,102
ABOUT $100,000.

00:21:44,670 --> 00:21:48,073
LISA, WHY AREN'T YOU
IN A LARGE RETAIL STORE?

00:21:48,073 --> 00:21:51,677
BECAUSE YOU'VE GONE TO THEM,
AND THEY'VE SAID TO YOU, WHAT?

00:21:51,677 --> 00:21:53,245
THERE'S THREE BOX RETAILERS

00:21:53,245 --> 00:21:55,581
THAT SELL 60% OF THE TOYS
IN THIS COUNTRY.
THAT'S RIGHT.

00:21:55,581 --> 00:21:57,616
YOU AND I KNOW BOTH KNOW THIS.
THAT'S RIGHT.

00:21:57,616 --> 00:22:00,486
WHAT DID THEY SAY TO YOU?
WHAT'D THEY SAY TO YOU?

00:22:00,486 --> 00:22:02,655
I HAVE NOT BROUGHT IT
TO ANY MASS RETAILERS.

00:22:02,655 --> 00:22:05,591
I'VE BEEN FOCUSING ON
THE BOUTIQUES FOR TWO REASONS.

00:22:05,591 --> 00:22:07,760
NUMBER ONE, I HAVEN'T HAD
THE CAPITAL TO BE ABLE TO GROW

00:22:07,760 --> 00:22:09,361
THE COMPANY AT THAT RATE,

00:22:09,361 --> 00:22:12,264
AND I DIDN'T WANT
TO PUT MY CART BEFORE MY HORSE.

00:22:12,264 --> 00:22:14,834
I WANTED TO MAKE SURE
WE HAD THE RIGHT PRODUCT,

00:22:14,834 --> 00:22:18,370
THE RIGHT MANUFACTURER.
BUT, LISA, WHY CAN'T YOU GO
TO A LARGE MASS RETAILER

00:22:18,370 --> 00:22:22,141
WITH THOSE THREE GUYS?
BECAUSE I'M UNDERCAPITALIZED.
I'VE GONE, I THINK,

00:22:22,141 --> 00:22:25,010
AS FAR AS I CAN WITHOUT
THE NEXT INFUSION OF CASH.

00:22:25,010 --> 00:22:27,446
(Daymond) HOW MUCH MORE
INVENTORY DO YOU HAVE REMAINING?

00:22:27,446 --> 00:22:30,716
I HAVE ABOUT, UH,
1,100 PIECES LEFT,

00:22:30,716 --> 00:22:35,054
AND I GET ORDERS EVERY DAY.
DO YOU BELIEVE THAT THOSE PIECES
ARE GONNA SELL THROUGH?

00:22:35,054 --> 00:22:37,056
THEY'RE ALREADY SOLD.
I HAVE A STACK OF ORDERS

00:22:37,056 --> 00:22:39,091
SITTING ON MY DESK
FOR FOURTH QUARTER

00:22:39,091 --> 00:22:41,493
THAT I HAVEN'T EVEN PUT
IN THE SYSTEM YET.

00:22:41,493 --> 00:22:44,563
YOU KNOW, ENGRAINED IN MY MIND
LIKE A LASER ARE THESE NUMBERS.

00:22:44,563 --> 00:22:48,133
TOYS‐‐$30 BILLION.

00:22:48,133 --> 00:22:50,636
PLUSH‐‐$2 BILLION.
I KNOW THIS MARKET INSIDE OUT.

00:22:50,636 --> 00:22:53,672
I ALSO KNOW HOW BRUTAL IT IS
TO GET DISTRIBUTION.

00:22:53,672 --> 00:22:56,542
LISA, IF I INVESTED
IN A TOY BUSINESS AGAIN,

00:22:56,542 --> 00:22:58,878
I WOULD WAKE UP
WITH NIGHTMARES.

00:22:58,878 --> 00:23:01,380
YOU'VE DONE A TERRIFIC JOB
OF PRESENTING IT,

00:23:01,380 --> 00:23:03,682
AND THERE'S NO QUESTION
IN MY MIND

00:23:03,682 --> 00:23:06,285
THAT THIS IS A GIANT
DISTRIBUTION JIGSAW PUZZLE.

00:23:06,285 --> 00:23:10,055
FOR ME, IT'S NOT A PLACE
I WANT TO BE IN. I'M OUT.

00:23:13,792 --> 00:23:17,196
LISA, THIS IS
WHERE I HAVE THE ISSUE‐‐

00:23:17,196 --> 00:23:19,431
WHEN IT'S AGE‐SPECIFIC...
MM‐HMM.

00:23:19,431 --> 00:23:22,601
YOU KNOW, 3 TO WHAT?
14.

00:23:22,601 --> 00:23:24,503
14, OKAY.
MM‐HMM.

00:23:24,503 --> 00:23:26,639
SO THAT'S‐‐THAT'S WHAT
I CALL A NICHE PRODUCT.

00:23:26,639 --> 00:23:28,641
OTHER THAN THE OTHER NICHE,
WHICH IS SEASONAL,

00:23:28,641 --> 00:23:31,277
THIS IS A‐A CHRISTMASTIME‐TYPE
PRODUCT,

00:23:31,277 --> 00:23:34,146
SO THE AGE
AND THE SEASONALITY OF IT

00:23:34,146 --> 00:23:36,415
ARE TWO STRIKES AGAINST
THE BUSINESS FOR ME.

00:23:36,415 --> 00:23:38,217
I'M OUT.

00:23:40,319 --> 00:23:42,521
LISA, WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO
WITH THE MONEY?

00:23:42,521 --> 00:23:44,957
ORDER MORE INVENTORY
TO HANDLE

00:23:44,957 --> 00:23:49,495
THE FOURTH QUARTER ORDERS
THAT I HAVE.
DO YOU HAVE THOSE ORDERS?
HARD COPY, FIRM?

00:23:49,495 --> 00:23:52,631
YES, SITTING ON MY DESK
RIGHT NOW. YES.

00:23:52,631 --> 00:23:54,700
LISA,

00:23:54,700 --> 00:23:57,536
I WOULD BE
VERY COMFORTABLE INVESTING...

00:23:59,138 --> 00:24:01,373
BUT ONLY $50,000,

00:24:01,373 --> 00:24:05,444
WHICH CREATES AN OPPORTUNITY,
BUT ALSO A PROBLEM FOR YOU.

00:24:05,444 --> 00:24:09,748
BUT I MUST HAVE
MY THIRD SHARE OF 50%.

00:24:09,748 --> 00:24:12,151
<i>BARBARA HAS MADE LISA AN OFFER,</i>

00:24:12,151 --> 00:24:15,554
<i>BUT ONLY FOR A THIRD</i>
<i>OF THE MONEY SHE NEEDS.</i>

00:24:15,554 --> 00:24:17,389
<i>LISA MUST GET ANOTHER SHARK</i>

00:24:17,389 --> 00:24:20,960
<i>TO GO IN ON THE DEAL</i>
<i>TO SECURE $150,000‐‐</i>

00:24:20,960 --> 00:24:23,262
<i>THE FULL AMOUNT</i>
<i>SHE'S ASKING FOR.</i>

00:24:25,197 --> 00:24:29,535
I HAVE THE POWER TO DO THIS DEAL
AND MAKE YOU FILTHY RICH,

00:24:29,535 --> 00:24:34,239
WHICH WOULD IN TURN,
MAKE ME RICHER.

00:24:34,239 --> 00:24:36,208
SOUNDS GOOD. (chuckles)

00:24:36,208 --> 00:24:38,210
I HAVE UNLIMITED
MANUFACTURING CAPABILITIES,

00:24:38,210 --> 00:24:40,713
SO IF YOU HAVE ORDERS
UP TO $10 BILLION,

00:24:40,713 --> 00:24:43,582
I COULD SHIP THAT TOMORROW.
THAT WOULD BE AWESOME.

00:24:43,582 --> 00:24:47,319
SO HERE'S WHAT I'M OFFERING‐‐
I WILL OFFER YOU

00:24:47,319 --> 00:24:50,389
ALL THE MANUFACTURING YOU WILL
EVER NEED AND DISTRIBUTION.

00:24:50,389 --> 00:24:52,057
YOU'LL HANDLE SALES.

00:24:52,057 --> 00:24:54,526
BUT I WOULD NEED 60%
OF THE COMPANY,

00:24:54,526 --> 00:24:59,465
BECAUSE YOU HAVE
NO MORE WORRIES AFTER THAT.

00:24:59,465 --> 00:25:02,634
NOW, BARBARA, IF YOU FEEL
YOU WANT TO COME IN...

00:25:02,634 --> 00:25:05,104
AM I BEING INVITED IN?
ARE YOU HAPPY TODAY, DAYMOND?

00:25:05,104 --> 00:25:07,339
GEE, I'M SUSPICIOUS.
YES, BARBARA.

00:25:07,339 --> 00:25:10,509
I'M GOING TO INVITE BARBARA
INTO MY SIDE OF THE DEAL.

00:25:10,509 --> 00:25:13,012
<i>LISA HAS AN OFFER</i>
<i>FROM DAYMOND AND BARBARA</i>

00:25:13,012 --> 00:25:15,481
<i>FOR $150,000,</i>

00:25:15,481 --> 00:25:18,617
<i>BUT FOR 60% OF HER COMPANY.</i>

00:25:18,617 --> 00:25:20,452
(Robert) HANG ON, LISA.

00:25:20,452 --> 00:25:24,390
I THINK THIS IS ALL CRAP.
I DON'T THINK THEY'RE BEING

00:25:24,390 --> 00:25:27,526
AS NICE TO YOU
AS THEY THINK THEY ARE.

00:25:27,526 --> 00:25:30,362
FUNDAMENTALLY,
THEY'RE GIVING YOU 150 GRAND

00:25:30,362 --> 00:25:32,331
FOR 60% OF YOUR BUSINESS.

00:25:32,331 --> 00:25:35,000
I'LL MAKE YOU AN OFFER.

00:25:35,000 --> 00:25:37,936
♪♪

00:25:43,675 --> 00:25:45,978
♪♪

00:25:45,978 --> 00:25:49,381
<i>DAYMOND AND BARBARA</i>
<i>HAVE OFFERED LISA $150,000</i>

00:25:49,381 --> 00:25:51,383
<i>FOR 60% OF HER COMPANY,</i>

00:25:51,383 --> 00:25:55,921
<i>BUT ROBERT MIGHT BE THROWING</i>
<i>A WRENCH INTO THE DEAL.</i>

00:25:55,921 --> 00:25:58,624
I'LL MAKE YOU AN OFFER.

00:25:58,624 --> 00:26:02,061
I'LL GIVE YOU $150,000 AS A LINE
OF CREDIT AGAINST ORDERS,

00:26:02,061 --> 00:26:04,063
'CAUSE THAT'S
WHAT YOU REALLY NEED.

00:26:04,063 --> 00:26:06,765
YOU JUST NEED CASH FLOW.

00:26:06,765 --> 00:26:09,034
IT'S THE SAME THING
THEY'RE GIVING YOU.

00:26:09,034 --> 00:26:12,938
AND I'LL GIVE YOU THAT
FOR NO EQUITY IN YOUR BUSINESS.

00:26:12,938 --> 00:26:15,741
WE'LL WORK OUT
A STANDARD LOAN RATE.

00:26:15,741 --> 00:26:18,177
IF ALL YOU NEED IS
A LITTLE BIT OF MONEY

00:26:18,177 --> 00:26:20,179
TO GET TO THE NEXT STEP,

00:26:20,179 --> 00:26:22,481
I'M HAPPY TO HELP YOU,
SIMPLY HELP YOU.

00:26:22,481 --> 00:26:25,050
AND HE CAN GO SELL
HIS GIRL SCOUT COOKIES.

00:26:25,050 --> 00:26:27,319
WHAT ARE WE DOING?

00:26:27,319 --> 00:26:29,788
SHE'S A GREAT LADY.
IF SHE NEEDS A HELPING HAND,

00:26:29,788 --> 00:26:32,291
I'M HAPPY TO BE THERE.
THE MONEY
IS NOT GONNA SOLVE IT.

00:26:32,291 --> 00:26:35,127
IT'S GONNA BE THE SHIPPING,
IT'S GONNA BE THE BILLING‐‐
(Robert) WELL, LISTEN‐‐

00:26:35,127 --> 00:26:37,129
IT'S GONNA BE‐‐
LET ME TALK.

00:26:37,129 --> 00:26:40,866
MIDNIGHT, WHEN IT'S LUNCHTIME
IN TAIWAN AND CHINA,

00:26:40,866 --> 00:26:43,569
AND WE'RE SLEEPING HERE,
THEY NEED CUSTOMS

00:26:43,569 --> 00:26:46,405
AND CLEARANCES
AND EVERYTHING ELSE.

00:26:46,405 --> 00:26:49,575
I'M OFFERING YOU EVERYTHING‐‐
THE WHOLE BACK OFFICE.

00:26:49,575 --> 00:26:51,743
THE VALUE WITH ME‐‐

00:26:51,743 --> 00:26:53,879
IT HELPS HER A LITTLE BIT
TO MOVE FORWARD,

00:26:53,879 --> 00:26:56,748
BUT SHE DOESN'T HAVE
TO GIVE UP ANY EQUITY.

00:26:56,748 --> 00:27:00,152
THE VALUE WITH YOU IS SHE HAS
TO GIVE UP 60% OF HER BUSINESS,

00:27:00,152 --> 00:27:03,789
BUT SHE MIGHT GET
MORE HELP LONG‐TERM.

00:27:03,789 --> 00:27:07,159
SO I THINK LISA NEEDS
TO DECIDE.
SO THIS IS
THE LOAN SHARK TANK?

00:27:07,159 --> 00:27:10,162
THAT'S WHAT YOU'RE DOING?
WHY DON'T WE LET HER DECIDE,
DAYMOND?

00:27:17,169 --> 00:27:19,538
I THINK THAT YOU'RE RIGHT.

00:27:19,538 --> 00:27:21,540
IF ALL I NEED IS MONEY,

00:27:21,540 --> 00:27:24,009
THAT THIS WOULD BE
THE BEST WAY TO GO‐‐

00:27:24,009 --> 00:27:26,345
A LINE OF CREDIT‐‐

00:27:26,345 --> 00:27:28,614
IF I ONLY NEEDED MONEY.

00:27:28,614 --> 00:27:31,450
UM, BUT IF I ONLY NEEDED
MONEY, I'D NEED A LOT MORE

00:27:31,450 --> 00:27:33,352
THAN $150,000.

00:27:33,352 --> 00:27:36,388
SO I THINK WHAT'S IN THE BEST
INTEREST OF THIS COMPANY

00:27:36,388 --> 00:27:38,690
AND WHERE‐‐WHAT IT NEEDS‐‐

00:27:38,690 --> 00:27:41,026
JUST PUT HIM
OUT OF HIS MISERY.

00:27:41,026 --> 00:27:44,062
IT WOULD BE BEST TO WORK
WITH THE TWO OF YOU.
THANK YOU.

00:27:44,062 --> 00:27:48,267
SO THANK YOU.
OH, THANK YOU SO MUCH.
I'M GONNA MAKE YOU RICH.
THANK YOU.

00:27:48,267 --> 00:27:50,903
THANK YOU SO MUCH.
THANK YOU.

00:27:50,903 --> 00:27:53,172
(Daymond) THE ROBIN HOOD CRAP
DOESN'T WORK WITH ME.

00:27:53,172 --> 00:27:55,007
(whispers) YEAH!

00:27:55,007 --> 00:27:56,708
OH!

00:27:56,708 --> 00:27:58,744
THANK YOU.

00:27:58,744 --> 00:28:02,281
I CAN'T HELP HER IN THE WAY
YOU CAN HELP HER.
WHAT IF YOU HAD MADE HER
SECOND‐GUESS IT?

00:28:02,281 --> 00:28:06,318
NO, YOU KNOW WHAT?
I JUST NEEDED HER TO BE SURE.
WHERE IS THIS COMING FROM?
DO YOU KNOW HER?

00:28:06,318 --> 00:28:10,455
I DON'T KNOW HER,
BUT I'VE BEEN WHERE SHE'S BEEN.
I JUST HOPE YOU'RE LIKE THIS
FOR EVERYBODY,

00:28:10,455 --> 00:28:12,791
BECAUSE THE NEXT TIME
I SEE SOMETHING LIKE THAT,

00:28:12,791 --> 00:28:16,094
I'M GONNA SAY, "ROB, STICK YOUR
NOSE IN IT AND JUST BE SO KIND."

00:28:16,094 --> 00:28:18,797
OOH, I'M SO SCARED, DAYMOND.
OOH!
"I'M SO KIND."

00:28:18,797 --> 00:28:22,067
I'M SO RELIEVED. THIS DEAL
IS GONNA CHANGE EVERYTHING.

00:28:22,067 --> 00:28:25,871
IT'S BEEN SO MANY SLEEPLESS
NIGHTS AND WORKING SO HARD.

00:28:25,871 --> 00:28:28,874
SO MANY PEOPLE IN MY LIFE
HAS SEEN HOW MUCH I'VE PUT UP,

00:28:28,874 --> 00:28:32,878
UM, PUT ON THE LINE FOR THIS,

00:28:32,878 --> 00:28:35,647
AND IT ALL CAME TOGETHER TODAY.

00:28:35,647 --> 00:28:38,650
<i>NEXT INTO THE SHARK TANK</i>
<i>IS EDWIN HEAVEN,</i>

00:28:38,650 --> 00:28:41,186
<i>WHO BELIEVES</i>
<i>HE HAS THE SOLUTION</i>

00:28:41,186 --> 00:28:43,922
<i>TO AN AGE‐OLD MYSTERY.</i>

00:28:43,922 --> 00:28:46,491
♪♪

00:28:52,164 --> 00:28:55,534
HELLO, HELLO, HELLO.
I'M EDWIN HEAVEN.

00:28:55,534 --> 00:28:57,402
I'M THE CREATOR OF THROX,

00:28:57,402 --> 00:29:00,906
THE CURE FOR THE MISSING SOCK.

00:29:00,906 --> 00:29:03,275
THROX LIKES TO DO THINGS
IN THREES,

00:29:03,275 --> 00:29:06,078
AND WE AIM TO PLEASE
IN THREES.

00:29:06,078 --> 00:29:08,714
AND I'M ASKING FOR $50,000

00:29:08,714 --> 00:29:12,718
IN EXCHANGE FOR 25% EQUITY.

00:29:12,718 --> 00:29:15,721
LET ME ASK YOU, WHAT DO YOU DO
WHEN YOU LOSE A SOCK?

00:29:15,721 --> 00:29:17,623
DO YOU SCREAM BLOODY MURDER?

00:29:17,623 --> 00:29:19,891
DO YOU KICK THE WASHER/DRYER?

00:29:19,891 --> 00:29:22,127
WELL, I HAVE A SOLUTION‐‐

00:29:22,127 --> 00:29:25,497
THROX‐‐THREE SOCKS.

00:29:25,497 --> 00:29:29,468
ONE, TWO, THREE.

00:29:29,468 --> 00:29:32,437
SO WHEN YOU LOSE ONE,

00:29:32,437 --> 00:29:34,439
YOU STILL HAVE A PAIR‐‐

00:29:34,439 --> 00:29:37,175
THE CURE FOR THE MISSING SOCK.

00:29:37,175 --> 00:29:41,113
THROX BEATS THE COMPETITION
BY A FOOT.

00:29:41,113 --> 00:29:42,914
<i>(gong crashes)</i>

00:29:42,914 --> 00:29:44,983
(chuckles)
(chuckles)

00:29:44,983 --> 00:29:47,552
EDWIN, I WONDER,
IS THIS A REAL PRODUCT

00:29:47,552 --> 00:29:52,057
OR IS THIS A CUTE GIFT ITEM

00:29:52,057 --> 00:29:55,260
THAT MY WIFE IS GONNA BUY
ONE TIME FOR OUR KIDS?

00:29:55,260 --> 00:29:57,863
NO, I BELIEVE
THAT THROX HAS LEGS.

00:29:59,598 --> 00:30:01,300
WHAT ARE YOUR SALES TODAY?

00:30:01,300 --> 00:30:05,637
MY SALES TODAY ARE $38,000.
FOR THE YEAR?

00:30:05,637 --> 00:30:09,608
FOR‐‐FOR THE YEAR. I'VE SOLD
8,500 UNITS THIS YEAR.

00:30:09,608 --> 00:30:13,178
I PREDICT 80,000 UNITS
IN 2010.

00:30:13,178 --> 00:30:16,081
LISTEN, EDWIN, IF YOU ACTUALLY
STARTED TO TAKE ANY MARKET SHARE

00:30:16,081 --> 00:30:18,650
FROM THE ESTABLISHED
SOCK MAKERS,

00:30:18,650 --> 00:30:22,187
THEY COULD CRUSH YOU LIKE
THE VAMPIRE COCKROACH YOU ARE

00:30:22,187 --> 00:30:24,623
IN TWO SECONDS.

00:30:24,623 --> 00:30:27,659
YOU HAVE NO SALES.
YOU HAVE‐‐

00:30:27,659 --> 00:30:30,862
YOU DON'T EVEN HAVE .001% SHARE
OF THIS MARKET.

00:30:30,862 --> 00:30:34,399
I ENTERED THE MARKET,
AND I HAD TO DO IT ALL MYSELF.

00:30:34,399 --> 00:30:37,135
OKAY, IF IT WORKS, AND YOUR
SALES GET TO $10 MILLION,

00:30:37,135 --> 00:30:40,472
AND I'M A LARGE SOCK GUY,
AND I SAY, "YOU KNOW,

00:30:40,472 --> 00:30:43,475
HEY, THERE'S THREE SOCKS HERE.
THEY'RE SELLING A LOT."
(snaps fingers)

00:30:43,475 --> 00:30:45,610
"GET MY SECRETARY IN HERE.

00:30:45,610 --> 00:30:47,612
"GET THE HEAD OF PRODUCTION
AND MARKETING.

00:30:47,612 --> 00:30:50,582
YOU SEE THIS? IT'S TAKING SHARE
FROM US. CRUSH THIS COCKROACH."

00:30:50,582 --> 00:30:54,052
HAVE YOU PATENTED THIS?
YOU CANNOT PATENT
A PACKAGE OF THREE SOCKS.

00:30:54,052 --> 00:30:55,954
RIGHT.

00:30:55,954 --> 00:30:58,557
I AM OUT.

00:30:58,557 --> 00:31:00,759
I SEE IT AS A NOVELTY PRODUCT.

00:31:00,759 --> 00:31:04,429
I CAN'T SEE YOU EVER MAKING
MONEY WITH THIS, SO I'M OUT.

00:31:05,964 --> 00:31:09,101
EDWIN, I'D LOVE TO BUY ONE
OR TWO FOR CHRISTMAS

00:31:09,101 --> 00:31:11,470
AND GET A SMILE
ON SOMEONE'S FACE,

00:31:11,470 --> 00:31:15,073
BUT I DON'T SEE IT AS A REPEAT
SALE, SO SADLY, I'M OUT.

00:31:16,708 --> 00:31:18,910
YOU KEEP DOING IT,

00:31:18,910 --> 00:31:20,912
