RIGHT NOW, THE RIGHT INVESTORS.

00:41:19,444 --> 00:41:20,979
IT'S REALLY A SHAME.

00:41:20,979 --> 00:41:24,182
SO I'M SO SAD TO SAY,
I'M OUT.

00:41:28,519 --> 00:41:31,990
YOU KNOW, I'VE GOTTA SAY...

00:41:31,990 --> 00:41:34,359
YOU'VE WASTED
YOUR OWN TIME TODAY,

00:41:34,359 --> 00:41:36,361
PUTTING A CRAZY NUMBER ON IT.

00:41:36,361 --> 00:41:38,363
THAT'S BECOME
VERY CLEAR TO YOU.

00:41:38,363 --> 00:41:41,165
I THINK YOU KNOW THAT NOW.
THAT WAS A MISTAKE.

00:41:41,165 --> 00:41:44,669
BUT WORSE?
YOU'VE WASTED MY TIME.

00:41:44,669 --> 00:41:46,771
I'M OUT.

00:41:46,771 --> 00:41:49,674
YOU REMIND ME OF ME
WHEN I STARTED.

00:41:49,674 --> 00:41:51,209
YOU ARE CONFIDENT.

00:41:51,209 --> 00:41:53,044
YOU'RE‐‐YOU'RE RUNNING
THE COMPANY.

00:41:53,044 --> 00:41:54,879
YOU'RE DESIGNING IT YOURSELF.

00:41:54,879 --> 00:41:58,349
BUT YOU'RE ASKING FOR JUST,
SOMETHING THAT WE CAN'T DO,

00:41:58,349 --> 00:42:00,251
AND THAT'S WHY WE'RE MAD.

00:42:00,251 --> 00:42:02,253
YOU WORKED SO HARD TO GET HERE,

00:42:02,253 --> 00:42:05,256
AND YOU WORKED SO HARD
TO DESTROY YOUR OPPORTUNITY,

00:42:05,256 --> 00:42:08,026
JUST BY THAT NUMBER.

00:42:08,026 --> 00:42:10,595
BECAUSE OF THE NUMBER,
I HAVE TO BE OUT.

00:42:10,595 --> 00:42:12,430
OKAY.

00:42:12,430 --> 00:42:14,565
YEAH, WE'RE ALL OUT.
THANK YOU.
WE'RE DONE.

00:42:14,565 --> 00:42:17,035
THANK YOU.
(Harrington) THAT'S IT.

00:42:17,035 --> 00:42:19,570
♪♪

00:42:19,570 --> 00:42:21,639
THE SHARKS COULDN'T SEE
THE BIG PICTURE.

00:42:21,639 --> 00:42:23,641
I DON'T REGRET GOING IN THERE

00:42:23,641 --> 00:42:25,643
ASKING FOR THE AMOUNT
WE ASKED FOR.

00:42:25,643 --> 00:42:27,645
I THINK THE SHARKS
DEFINITELY LOST OUT TODAY.

00:42:27,645 --> 00:42:30,915
I THINK THEY MISSED IT TODAY.
THEY MISSED A BIG OPPORTUNITY.

00:42:30,915 --> 00:42:34,085
I LIKE THE GUY.
HE'S A PIG, THOUGH.

00:42:34,085 --> 00:42:37,355
THERE'S NO WAY THAT COMPANY
IS WORTH $2 MILLION.
NOT A CHANCE.

00:42:37,355 --> 00:42:40,358
ALL RIGHT. HE'S GONE.
HE'S DEAD. HE'S VAPOR.

00:42:40,358 --> 00:42:44,095
I'LL NEVER THINK OF HIM AGAIN,
EVEN WHEN I LOOK AT MY BELT.
BUT YOU HAVE A BELT BUCKLE.

00:42:44,095 --> 00:42:46,831
I KNOW, FROM A DEAD MAN.
(laughs)

00:42:46,831 --> 00:42:48,199
(chuckles)

00:42:54,705 --> 00:42:56,541
<i>NEXT WEEK ON "SHARK TANK"...</i>

00:42:56,541 --> 00:42:59,710
IS IT POSSIBLE
THAT LARGER‐SIZE WOMEN

00:42:59,710 --> 00:43:01,879
DON'T CARE ABOUT FASHION
AS MUCH?

00:43:01,879 --> 00:43:04,749
YOU ARE REALLY RUTHLESS.
YOU ARE REALLY RIGHT.

00:43:04,749 --> 00:43:07,785
I... DON'T KNOW THAT MUCH
ABOUT THE BEVERAGE INDUSTRY.
OOH.

00:43:07,785 --> 00:43:10,688
THAT'S NOT SOMETHING
YOU SHOULD'VE JUST SAID TO ME.

00:43:10,688 --> 00:43:13,191
ARE YOU CUTTING HIM A CHECK?
I AM GONNA WRITE YOU A CHECK.

00:43:13,191 --> 00:43:15,893
(O'Leary) NO!
ARE YOU CRAZY?
GIVE ME THE MONEY.

00:43:15,893 --> 00:43:18,796
YOU MUST BE OUT OF YOUR MIND.
DON'T DO IT.
DON'T DO IT.

00:43:18,796 --> 00:43:21,099
I'LL GIVE YOU $20,000
FOR THERAPY.

00:43:21,099 --> 00:43:23,568
(laughs)
OH, MY. MY, MY, MY.

